This is a '''list of people from the [[University of Oxford]] involved in education'''. Many were students at one (or more) of the [[Colleges of the University of Oxford|colleges]] of the University, and others held [[Oxbridge Fellowship|fellowships]] at a college. Some are known for their involvement in schools, including [[Thomas Arnold]], Headmaster of [[Rugby School]] and [[Anthony Chenevix-Trench]], Headmaster of [[Eton College]]. Others for their work with universities or educational administration, such as [[Jack Butterworth, Baron Butterworth|Lord Butterworth]], the founding [[Vice-Chancellor]] of [[University of Warwick]]. University professors and lecturers who are primarily known for their work in their specialist field are found in other lists. This list forms part of a series of lists of people associated with the University of Oxford &ndash; for other lists, please see the main article [[List of University of Oxford people]].
